org.openbel.framework.core.df.cache
Interface CacheLookupService

All Known Implementing Classes:
DefaultCacheLookupService
public interface CacheLookupService

CacheLookupService defines service-level lookup operations to the BELFramework cache defined at SystemConfiguration.getCacheDirectory().

Author:
Anthony Bargnesi <abargnesi@selventa.com>

Method Detail

findInCache

CachedResource findInCache(ResourceType resourceType,
                           String location)
Retrieves the cached resource for the location.

Parameters:
resourceType - ResourceType, the resource type of the location provided, which cannot be null
location - String, the remote resource location, which cannot be null
Returns:
CachedResource the cache entry for the resource location or null if the resource is not in the cache
Throws:
InvalidArgument - Thrown if the location or resourceType is null

getResources

List<CachedResource> getResources()
Retrieves all resources that are present in the cache.

Returns:
List of CachedResource, the list of resources present in the cache, which might be empty
